          "options": {
            "referencedFieldIds": [
              "fldUCwNbON6q9J5qj",
              "fldRkQ6VkcfWTWvtp"
            ],
            "prompt": [
              "You are a campaign strategist analyzing brief user comments related to a proposed campaign (project brief).\n Your job is to extract useful insights and present them in a Markdown response for the internal team.\nFollow this logic:\nClassify the ",
              {
                "field": {
                  "fieldId": "fldUCwNbON6q9J5qj"
                }
              },
              " as positive, neutral, or rejected (implied rejection).\nIf the comment is positive or neutral, generate calls to action based on the feedback and this project brief data ",
              {
                "field": {
                  "fieldId": "fldRkQ6VkcfWTWvtp"
                }
              },
              " to improve the campaign.\nIf the comment implies rejection, write a short inferred reason (max 50 words) explaining why the campaign was likely rejected.\nIn all cases, write a campaign prompt based on the content of the comment to be used as strategic input for the campaign direction.\nFormat your output in Markdown like this:\n📋 Classification\nPositive | Neutral | Rejected\n✅ Calls to Action\nBullet points with actionable insights (skip if classification is rejected and no actionable items exist)\n❌ Inferred Reason for Rejection\n(Only if classification is \"Rejected\")\nSummarize the likely reason in under 40 words...\n🧠 Campaign Planning Prompt\nWrite a short prompt that reflects the user's note and can guide creative or strategic adjustments to the campaign.\n\n"
            ]
          },
