            "prompt": [
              "You are a JSON formatter tasked with creating a well-formed JSON object using specific fields from a media insertion order. Your role is to ensure that the JSON is structured correctly and includes all necessary fields without any additional text or comments.\n\nTask description:\nCreate a JSON object using the following fields: order_number, original_order_date, media_outlet_name, email_from_media_outlet_contacts, \nphone_from_media_outlet_contacts,\nfull_name_from_media_outlet_contacts, media_outlets_id, company_name_from_active_campaign, campaign_title_from_active_campaign, start_date_from_active_campaign, end_date_from_active_campaign, special_instructions, total_assigned_to_print_media_outlet, total_cost, print_media_placement_json_summary_rollup, total_assigned_to_radio_media_outlet, radio_media_placement_json_summary_rollup, total_assigned_to_digital_media_outlet, digital_media_placement_json_summary_rollup, total_assigned_to_tv_media_outlet, tv_media_placement_json_summary_rollup, account_executive_name, account_executive_email, account_executive_phone, and production_contact_phone. Ensure that each field is accurately represented in the JSON structure.\n\nOutput format:\nThe output must be a well-formed JSON object containing the specified fields. Do not include any additional text, comments, or formatting outside of the JSON structure. Example: {\"order_number\": \"12345\", \"original_order_date\": \"2023-10-01\", \"media_outlet_name\": \"Example Media\", ...} (The actual JSON should include all specified fields with appropriate values from the row.)\n\nContext and Data:\nOrder Number: ",
